@startuml StudentRent-DBDiagram-v1_6-student-profile
' PROMPT v1.6: DB Diagram 2 — Student Profile Layer
' Business layer: students save reusable application profiles (Prototype source)

title DB Diagram 2: Student Profile Layer (v1.6)

hide empty members
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam linetype ortho

skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor<<table>> #E3F2FD
    BorderColor<<table>> #1565C0
    BackgroundColor<<ghost>> #F5F5F5
    BorderColor<<ghost>> #BDBDBD
}

package "Student Profile Layer" {

    entity "RentalApplicationProfiles" <<table>> {
        **Id** : uniqueidentifier <<PK>>
        --
        ProfileName : nvarchar(80) <<NOT NULL>>
        ApplicantName : nvarchar(120) <<NOT NULL>>
        Phone : nvarchar(40) <<NOT NULL>>
        Email : nvarchar(254) <<NOT NULL>>
        Message : nvarchar(2000)
        CreatedAtUtc : datetime2 <<NOT NULL>>
        UpdatedAtUtc : datetime2 <<NOT NULL>>
        --
        <<IX>> IX_RentalApplicationProfiles_ProfileName (ProfileName)
        <<IX>> IX_RentalApplicationProfiles_UpdatedAtUtc (UpdatedAtUtc)
    }
}

package "Housing Catalog Layer (reference)" <<ghost>> {

    entity "RentalApplications" <<ghost>> {
        **Id** : uniqueidentifier <<PK>>
        --
        ApplicantName : nvarchar(120)
        Phone : nvarchar(40)
        Email : nvarchar(254)
        Message : nvarchar(2000)
        ...
    }
}

RentalApplicationProfiles ..> RentalApplications : "Prototype Clone()\n(no FK, data flow\nvia application layer)"

note bottom of RentalApplicationProfiles
    **Prototype source (v1.4):**
    Profile data is cloned into
    RentalApplications at runtime.
    No database-level FK exists —
    the relationship is enforced
    by application logic.
end note

note right of RentalApplicationProfiles
    **CRUD via SP:**
    sp_RentalApplicationProfiles_Create
    sp_RentalApplicationProfiles_GetById
    sp_RentalApplicationProfiles_GetAll
    sp_RentalApplicationProfiles_Update
    sp_RentalApplicationProfiles_Delete
end note

@enduml
